    <div class="newsentry__header">
        <p>Exhibition</p>
        <h3><a href="../2013/10/29/madame-wu-and-the-mill-from-hell/index.html">Madame Wu and the Mill from Hell</a></h3>
        <p>The British School at Rome, Italy</p>
        <p>29 October - 19 November 2013</p>
        <p><a href="http://www.bsr.ac.uk/madame-wu-and-the-mill-from-hell">bsr.ac.uk</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="newsentry__text">

        <p>Caruso St John and Thomas Demand have collaborated for many years. In this exhibition for the British School at Rome they present, for the first time, an analysis of some of their work together. Projects exhibited include: Thomas Demand’s exhibition at the <em>Nationalgalerie,</em> Berlin, 2009; <em>Nagelhaus</em>, the redesign of the Escher-Wyss-Platz, Zurich, 2007-2010 and <em>Thomas Demand’s house</em>, near Berlin, that has just been completed in the summer of 2013. The exhibition is open until Tuesday 19th November.</p>

        

    </div>

    

</div>

        
